# P.A.T.A.N.G. — Deep Onboarding Audit Report

> **Date:** 2026-03-22 | **Auditor:** Principal Architect Review | **Repo:** Patang (backend-only)

---

## 1. Executive Summary

P.A.T.A.N.G. is a **backend-only Node.js/Express API** for IIT Kanpur's campus resource management. There is **no frontend in the repository** — only the backend API server exists. The codebase is reasonably well-structured and implements a substantial portion of the SRS, with particular depth in sports facility booking, gym/swim subscriptions, caretaker operations, and event management.

**Key findings:**
- **Stack matches SRS:** Node.js + Express + MongoDB + OTP auth + QR systems ✔
- **Frontend is absent:** ReactJS (specified in SRS) is not present
- **V1/V2 dual-model pattern** creates significant technical debt — two parallel schemas for Bookings and Subscriptions
- **Executive Portal is partially scaffolded** — executives can review events and subscriptions, but there is **no dedicated executive dashboard or unified executive portal**
- **9 user roles** are defined, but only some have dedicated portals/routes
- **No automated test suite** exists
- **CORS is fully open** (`app.use(cors())`) — security concern for production

---

## 2. System Architecture Overview

### Project Type
Backend-only REST API monolith. No frontend, no microservices.

### Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology | Version |
|-------|-----------|---------|
| Runtime | Node.js | ESM modules (`"type": "module"`) |
| Framework | Express.js | v5.2.1 |
| Database | MongoDB via Mongoose | v9.3.0 |
| Auth | JWT (jsonwebtoken) | v9.0.3 |
| Password hashing | bcryptjs | v3.0.3 |
| File uploads | Multer | v2.1.1 |
| QR generation | qrcode | v1.5.4 |
| Email | Nodemailer | v8.0.2 |
| Cron jobs | node-cron | v4.2.1 |
| Date handling | dayjs | v1.11.20 |
| UUID | uuid | v13.0.0 |
| Package manager | npm (lock file present) | — |

### API Style
REST, with a dual versioning scheme:
- **V1:** `/api/auth`, `/api/facilities`, `/api/bookings`, `/api/subscriptions`
- **V2:** `/api/v2/facilities`, `/api/v2/bookings`, `/api/v2/subscriptions`, `/api/v2/events`, `/api/v2/admin/*`
- **Page-optimized endpoints:** `/api/dashboard`, `/api/slot-booking/*`, `/api/history/*`, `/api/calendar`, `/api/settings`, `/api/coordinator/*`, `/api/feedback`

### Directory Architecture

```
backend/
├── package.json          # Dependencies, ESM config
├── src/
│   ├── server.js         # Entry: dotenv, MongoDB connect, app.listen
│   ├── app.js            # Express app: CORS, routes, cron job init
│   ├── controllers/      # 17 files — all business logic
│   ├── models/           # 15 Mongoose schemas
│   ├── routes/           # 18 Express routers
│   ├── middlewares/      # 3 files: auth, upload, validation
│   ├── services/         # 7 files: reusable business logic
│   ├── utils/            # 5 files: helpers, token gen, email
│   └── jobs/             # 4 cron job definitions
```

### Entry Points & Initialization Flow
1. [server.js](file:///c:/Users/HP/Patang/backend/src/server.js) → loads `.env`, connects to MongoDB, starts Express
2. [app.js](file:///c:/Users/HP/Patang/backend/src/app.js) → mounts CORS, JSON parser, static file serving, all 18 route groups, starts 4 cron jobs
3. All cron jobs start with `.start()` at import time in [app.js](file:///c:/Users/HP/Patang/backend/src/app.js)

### State Management
Stateless JWT-based auth. No server-side sessions. All state in MongoDB.

### Environment Configuration
- `MONGO_URI` — MongoDB connection string
- `JWT_SECRET` — JWT signing key (also reused for QR token signing)
- `PORT` — server port (default 5000)
- `EMAIL_HOST`, `EMAIL_PORT`, `EMAIL_USER`, `EMAIL_PASS` — SMTP for OTP emails (implied by nodemailer usage)

