*\* `gym_admin`/`swim_admin` are scoped to their respective facility types via [getScopedSubscriptionTypes()](file:///c:/Users/HP/Patang/backend/src/services/accessService.js#25-46)*

### Authorization Enforcement
- **Mechanism:** Two-layer middleware chain: [protectRoute](file:///c:/Users/HP/Patang/backend/src/middlewares/authMiddleware.js#4-22) (JWT verification) → [authorizeRoles(...)](file:///c:/Users/HP/Patang/backend/src/middlewares/authMiddleware.js#23-33) (role check)
- **[protectRoute](file:///c:/Users/HP/Patang/backend/src/middlewares/authMiddleware.js#4-22):** Extracts Bearer token, verifies JWT, populates `req.user` from DB
- **[authorizeRoles](file:///c:/Users/HP/Patang/backend/src/middlewares/authMiddleware.js#23-33):** Checks `req.user.roles.some(role => allowedRoles.includes(role))`
- **Scoping (facility-specific):** [getScopedSubscriptionTypes()](file:///c:/Users/HP/Patang/backend/src/services/accessService.js#25-46) further constrains `gym_admin` and `swim_admin`

### Security Observations

> [!WARNING]
> - **Cancel booking has no role restriction** — `DELETE /api/v2/bookings/:bookingId` only applies [protectRoute](file:///c:/Users/HP/Patang/backend/src/middlewares/authMiddleware.js#4-22), meaning any authenticated user can attempt cancellation (ownership is checked in controller code, not middleware)
> - **`coach` role is defined** in the User schema but has **zero dedicated routes** — functionally identical to `student`
> - **JWT `expiresIn: '30d'`** — very long token lifetime with no refresh mechanism or revocation list
> - **CORS is fully open** — `app.use(cors())` allows all origins
> - **`JWT_SECRET` reused for QR tokens** — separate secrets would be safer
> - **No rate limiting** on any endpoint (auth, booking, etc.)
> - No CSRF protection (stateless JWT mitigates this somewhat)

