## 7. Executive Portal Readiness Analysis

### What Executive Functionality Already Exists

| Capability | Endpoint | Status |
|-----------|---------|--------|
| Review pending events | `GET /api/v2/admin/events/pending` | ✔ Works |
| Approve/reject/request-changes events | `PATCH /api/v2/admin/events/:eventId` | ✔ Works |
| Review subscription applications | `GET /api/v2/admin/subscriptions` | ✔ Works |
| Approve/reject subscriptions | `PATCH /api/v2/admin/subscriptions/:id` | ✔ Works |
| View occupancy | `GET /api/v2/admin/subscriptions/occupancy` | ✔ Works |
| Verify entry (QR scan) | `POST /api/v2/subscriptions/verify-entry` | ✔ Works |
| View feedback inbox | `GET /api/feedback/inbox` | ✔ Works (targets `executive` + `general`) |
| Reply to feedback | `PATCH /api/feedback/:id/reply` | ✔ Works |
| Coordinator portal access | `GET/POST /api/coordinator/*` | ✔ Executive role included |
| Create bookings | `POST /api/v2/bookings` | ✔ Executive role included |

### What Is Missing for a Dedicated Executive Portal

1. **No unified executive dashboard** — executives must hit separate endpoints
2. **No venue booking approval/rejection endpoint** — FacilityBlocks with `pending` status have no review API
3. **No cross-module analytics** — no aggregate stats endpoint
4. **No user/role management** — cannot assign or remove roles
5. **No facility management CRUD** — cannot create/edit/disable facilities
6. **No penalty management** — cannot view/clear/modify penalties for users
7. **No system configuration** — cannot modify booking rules, plan pricing, etc. via API

### Dependencies for Executive Portal

```mermaid
graph TD
    EP["Executive Portal"] --> Events["Event Review (exists)"]
    EP --> Subs["Subscription Review (exists)"]
    EP --> Venues["Venue Approval (MISSING)"]
    EP --> Feedback["Feedback Inbox (exists)"]
    EP --> Dashboard["Unified Dashboard (MISSING)"]
    EP --> Analytics["Analytics (MISSING)"]
    EP --> UserMgmt["User Management (MISSING)"]
    EP --> FacilityMgmt["Facility CRUD (MISSING)"]
    EP --> PenaltyMgmt["Penalty Management (MISSING)"]
```

### Integration Points
- **Event model** — `status`, `reviewedBy`, `reviewedAt` fields already support executive actions
- **SubscriptionV2** — `reviewedBy`, `reviewedAt`, `reviewComments` ready
- **FacilityBlock** — `approvedBy` field exists but is never populated
- **Feedback** — `targetRole: 'executive'` routing already works
- **User model** — `roles` array can be updated but no admin API exists

### Merge Conflict Risk Areas
- [app.js](file:///c:/Users/HP/Patang/backend/src/app.js) — every new route group requires a mount point here
- [authMiddleware.js](file:///c:/Users/HP/Patang/backend/src/middlewares/authMiddleware.js) — any changes to role logic affect all modules
- Route files for admin endpoints if multiple developers add executive routes simultaneously

