## 8. Collaboration Risk Map

### High Change-Frequency Areas
| File/Area | Risk | Reason |
|-----------|------|--------|
| [app.js](file:///c:/Users/HP/Patang/backend/src/app.js) | 🔴 High | Every feature adds route mounts here |
| [authMiddleware.js](file:///c:/Users/HP/Patang/backend/src/middlewares/authMiddleware.js) | 🔴 High | Shared across all protected endpoints |
| [User.js](file:///c:/Users/HP/Patang/backend/src/models/User.js) model | 🟡 Medium | Role additions require enum update + migration |
| [validate.js](file:///c:/Users/HP/Patang/backend/src/middlewares/validate.js) | 🟡 Medium | All validation in one file |

### Shared Components Causing Clashes
- **V1/V2 controllers query the same models** — `dashboardController`, `historyController`, `slotBookingController` all query both [Booking](file:///c:/Users/HP/Patang/backend/src/controllers/bookingControllerV2.js#245-300) and [SportsBooking](file:///c:/Users/HP/Patang/backend/src/controllers/slotBookingController.js#83-311)
- **[bookingService.js](file:///c:/Users/HP/Patang/backend/src/services/bookingService.js)** — shared by booking creation and dashboard fair-use logic
- **[accessService.js](file:///c:/Users/HP/Patang/backend/src/services/accessService.js)** — shared by subscription admin, entry verification, and occupancy

### Global State Risks
- **Cron jobs run in-process** — if one job crashes, it could affect the Express event loop
- **No connection pooling config** — Mongoose defaults

### Database Schema Coupling
- **V1/V2 field naming inconsistency:** [Booking](file:///c:/Users/HP/Patang/backend/src/controllers/bookingControllerV2.js#245-300) uses `userId/facilityId/slotId`, [SportsBooking](file:///c:/Users/HP/Patang/backend/src/controllers/slotBookingController.js#83-311) uses `user/facility/slot` — any shared query builder must handle both
- **`AccessLog.facilityType`** enum allows BOTH lowercase (`gym`, `swimming`) AND PascalCase ([Gym](file:///c:/Users/HP/Patang/backend/src/controllers/slotBookingController.js#316-415), `SwimmingPool`) — data inconsistency risk in aggregation
- **`Penalty.bookingId`** references [Booking](file:///c:/Users/HP/Patang/backend/src/controllers/bookingControllerV2.js#245-300) model only — V2 [SportsBooking](file:///c:/Users/HP/Patang/backend/src/controllers/slotBookingController.js#83-311) penalties are not tracked

### Inconsistent Patterns
- Response format: some controllers return `{ success, data }` via [apiResponse.js](file:///c:/Users/HP/Patang/backend/src/utils/apiResponse.js), others return raw `{ message }` (auth controller)
- Error handling: auth controller uses `res.status().json()`, everything else uses `errorResponse()`
- Naming: `cancelledAt` vs absence of consistent cancellation tracking across V1/V2

