## 9. Critical Technical Debt

| Item | Severity | Detail |
|------|----------|--------|
| V1/V2 dual models | 🔴 High | Two parallel schemas for Bookings and Subscriptions. Dashboard/history must merge both. |
| No tests | 🔴 High | `"test": "echo \"Error: no test specified\""` — zero automated tests |
| CORS wide open | 🔴 High | `app.use(cors())` with no origin restriction |
| No rate limiting | 🟡 Medium | Auth endpoints (login, register, OTP) vulnerable to brute force |
| JWT reused for QR | 🟡 Medium | `JWT_SECRET` used for both auth tokens and QR tokens |
| 30-day token lifetime | 🟡 Medium | No refresh flow, no token revocation |
| AccessPass model orphaned | 🟡 Medium | V1 `AccessPass` references [Subscription](file:///c:/Users/HP/Patang/backend/src/controllers/subscriptionControllerV2.js#56-70), never used by V2 flow |
| Venue approval gap | 🟡 Medium | FacilityBlock approval endpoint not implemented |
| No input sanitization | 🟡 Medium | Beyond basic validation, no XSS/injection sanitization |
| [name](file:///c:/Users/HP/Patang/backend/src/middlewares/upload.js#17-22) field on User not required at registration | 🟢 Low | [registerUser](file:///c:/Users/HP/Patang/backend/src/controllers/authController.js#5-52) doesn't collect name; User model requires it — potential save error |
| Data URL QR stored in DB | 🟢 Low | Full base64 images in `SubscriptionV2.qrCode` — storage bloat |

